Utilities.doc

GroundhoGrafix Utilities Document


This document explains the usage of the
utility programs written by
GroundhoGrafix for Power C.


Hint: The Runstop key brings up the
command line. Type: /utilityname and
hit F3 to quickly find the utility name
in this document.


The first section of this document
provides quick informaion about the
utilities. The second section provides
details on where the source files are
located for modification or review.

Utilities
-------------------
prasc2sc.sh
Location: utility01
Description: Prints a C array/table to a
  file that allows you to convert
  PETSCII to screen codes. Just include
  the output file in your C program and
  you can easily reference it using the
  PETSCII code to find the appropriate 
  Screen Code.


Source:
-------------------
prasc2sc
Location: Utility01wd (wd=work disk)
Files: stdio.h
       conio.h
       prasc2sc.c

Link: prasc2sc.o
      ^
